news.title: Sweden's SBB posts $479.65 million pretax loss in Q4 2023
news.para: The landlord, which owns properties across Sweden including hospitals and care homes, reported a fourth quarter pre-tax loss of 4.93 billion Swedish crowns ($479.65 million), compared to a loss of a revised 8.03 billion crowns a year ago.

news.title: Swedish landlord Heimstaden Bostad posts pre-tax loss for Q4 2023
news.para: The unlisted subsidiary of Heimstaden AB reported a loss before tax of 1.52 billion Swedish crowns ($147.86 million) for the fourth quarter, compared to the loss of 12.97 billion crowns it reported a year earlier.

news.title: Punjab government says no need for NOC to sell land in unplanned rural areas
news.para: It is a known fact that the area falling under the abadi deh is not under the planned area. The Punjab Apartment and Property Regulation Act excludes any such area.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: 51 cities to be governed by new GIS-based master plan
news.para: The housing department on Monday sought the status of the GIS-based master plans being readied by the concerned regulatory authorities.

news.title: Builders Association of India protests hike in construction material prices in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: At least 15,000 construction workers participated in the demonstration that was held in front of the Red Cross building in the city.

news.title: Maharashtra allocates Rs 10,519 crore towards land acquisition for Pune outer ring road
news.para: MSRDC officials confirmed that they had demanded the amount allocated in the state budget. The officials are hopeful of completion of land acquisition by June.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh HC sets aside CRDA’s plot relocation notification
news.para: The court also set aside the notices issued by CRDA to farmers cancelling the original allotment of plots on lands not covered under the land pooling scheme (LPS) and are yet to be acquired.

news.title: Bombay HC saves building proposal from ‘Kafkaesque’ BMC
news.para: Gufran Qureshi (38), plot owner and builder who questioned the sudden denial of permission last Dec and this Jan by the civic engineer, informed the high court that the building is constructed up to seven floors.

news.title: Delhi civic body seals six shops under sealing drive in Connaught place
news.para: The drive was carried out in Connaught Place's B, C, D and G blocks. Atul Bhargava, president of the New Delhi Traders' Association, demanded that there should be a uniform tax regime across Delhi.

news.title: Telangana government likely to reject over three lakh LRS applications
news.para: Of the 25 lakh applications, majority of the rejected ones were in Greater Hyderabad Municipal Corporation (GHMC) and surrounding municipal corporations, according to official sources.

news.title: SC asks five DMs in Tamil Nadu to appear before ED in illegal sand mining probe
news.para: The Supreme Court has directed five district collectors of Tamil Nadu to appear before the Enforcement Directorate in connection with a money laundering probe related to alleged illegal sand mining.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government exempts DMRC & NCRTC from paying municipal taxes
news.para: A GMC official said, “We said in our plea that a central govt rule mandates municipalities across the country to levy service charges on all central and state govt buildings and installations instead of services that a municipality provides.

news.title: Ashiana Housing to invest Rs 400 crore to develop senior living project in Chennai
news.para: "The investment for Ashiana Vatsalya is primarily funded through internal resources, supplemented by a loan of 8-10%," said Ankur Gupta, joint managing director of Ashiana Housing

news.title: China's Country Garden faces liquidation petition
news.para: Country Garden said in a regulatory filing to the Hong Kong Stock Exchange it would "resolutely" oppose the petition, which was filed by a creditor, Ever Credit Limited, a unit of Kingboard Holdings. A court hearing had been set for May 17.

news.title: Essentials can be denied to defaulters under apartments act: Telangana HC
news.para: Telangana high court supported the powers of apartment associations under the Telangana Apartments Act. The court stated that apartment associations need funds for maintaining the premises and dealing with defaulters.

news.title: Delhi civic body to not extend deadline for property geo-tagging
news.para: It has also issued a public notice in this regard, explaining that there is no plan to extend the deadline of Feb 29 for taxpayers wanting to avail 10% rebate on advance payment of property tax.

news.title: IL&FS puts over 5.4 lakh sq ft GIFT City office properties on the block
news.para: Beleaguered non-banking finance company IL&FS is selling commercial properties in GIFT TWO, Gujarat’s GIFT City, as part of its debt resolution process. The properties include offices leased to Tata Consultancy Services.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Kharavela Enclave buyers protest against delay in handing over of flats
news.para: The homebuyers said the OSHB had taken up the project in 2011 with a promise to hand over completed apartments by 2014. However, 10 years have passed but the board is yet to give them the flats.
